The Trial Chamber has announced that evidentiary hearings in Case 002/02 against Khieu Samphan and Nuon Chea will commence on 17 October 2014 at 09:00. 
The Co-Prosecutors will be allowed to make a brief opening statement and the Accused will be given an oppurtunity to respond,before the first witness will be called to testify on Monday 20 October.
Unless otherwise specified, the Chamber will sit three days each week following the same daily schedule as in Case 002/01, beginning each day at 9:00 am and ending at 4:00 pm with a lunch break from 12:00 pm to 1:30 pm and a morning and afternoon break as determined by the President.
The schedule will be revisited after the parties have filed their appeal briefs in Case 002/01.